.TH sdl2trs 1 "2026-05-17" "sdl2trs 1.2.35"
.SH NAME
sdl2trs \- TRS-80 Model I/III/4/4P emulator for SDL2
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sdl2trs
[\fIfile.t8c\fP] [\fIfile.t8s\fP] [\fIfile.cmd\fP] [\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sdl2trs
is an emulator for Tandy/Radio Shack line of Zilog Z80-based
microcomputers popular in late 1970s and early 1980s.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-a(spect)(ratio)
Keep TRS-80 screen aspect ratio when resizing SDL2 window (Default).
.TP
\fB\-b(ack)g(round)\fP \fI0xRRGGBB\fP
Specifies background color of emulator window.
\fIRRGGBB\fP are hex values of Red, Green, and Blue components.
Default: black (\fI0x000000\fP).
.TP
\fB\-b(order)w(idth)\fP \fIwidth\fP
Put border of \fIwidth\fP pixels (0 - 50) around TRS-80 window.
Default: \fI2\fP.
.TP
\fB\-c(ass)d(ir)\fP \fIdir\fP
Specify directory containing cassette and stringy wafer images.
Default: current directory.
.TP
\fB\-c(assette)\fP \fIfilename\fP
Specifies name of cassette image file to be inserted into
emulated cassette drive.
.TP
\fB\-c(har)s(et)\fP \fIcharset-name\fP
Use charset of the selected TRS-80 Model with \fB-m(odel)\fP.
.TP
\fB\-c(har)s(et)1\fP \fIcharset-name\fP
Select Model I charset:
\fIc(t-80)\fP |
\fIe(arly)\fP |
\fIg(enie)\fP |
\fIh(t-1080z)\fP |
\fIl(cmod)\fP |
\fIm(eritum)\fP |
\fIs(tock)\fP |
\fIv(ideogenie)\fP |
\fIw(ider)\fP.
Default: \fIwider\fP.
.TP
\fB\-c(har)s(et)3\fP \fIcharset-name\fP
.TQ
\fB\-c(har)s(et)4\fP \fIcharset-name\fP
Select Model III/4/4P charset:
\fIk(atakana)\fP |
\fIi(nternational)\fP |
\fIb(old)\fP.
Defaults are \fIkatakana\fP for Model III and \fIinternational\fP
for Model 4/4P.
.TP
\fB\-cl(ock)\fP \fIMHz\fP
Set clock speed in MHz of the selected TRS-80 Model with \fB-m(odel)\fP.
.TP
\fB\-cl(ock)1\fP \fIMHz\fP
.TQ
\fB\-cl(ock)3\fP \fIMHz\fP
.TQ
\fB\-cl(ock)4\fP \fIMHz\fP
Set clock speed rate in MHz for the specified TRS-80 Model.
Defaults are:
\fI1.77408\fP MHz for Model I,
\fI2.02752\fP MHz for Model III and
\fI4.05504\fP MHz for Model 4/4P.
.TP
\fB\-debug\fP | \fB-z(bx)\fP
Enter zbx debugger (Optional).
.TP
\fB\-di(skdebug)\fP \fIhexval\fP
Set floppy disk controller debug flags to hex value:
\fI01\fP = FDC register I/O |
\fI02\fP = FDC commands |
\fI04\fP = VTOS 3.0 JV3 kludges |
\fI08\fP = Gaps |
\fI10\fP = Phys sector sizes |
\fI20\fP = Readadr timing |
\fI40\fP = DMK |
\fI80\fP = ioctl errors.
.TP
\fB\-d(isk)\fP\fIN filename\fP
Specifies name of floppy disk image file to be inserted into
Disk\fIN\fP (0 - 7).
.TP
\fB\-d(isk)d(ir)\fP \fIdir\fP
Specify directory containing floppy disk images.
Default: current directory.
.TP
\fB\-d(isk)s(et)\fP \fIfilename\fP
Loads diskset from \fIfilename\fP into emulator.
.TP
\fB\-d(isk)s(et)d(ir)\fP \fIdir\fP
Specify directory containing diskset files.
Default: current directory.
.TP
\fB\-d(oubler)\fP \fItype\fP
Specify type of double density adaptor to emulate for Model I:
\fIp(ercom)\fP |
\fIt(andy)\fP |
\fIb(oth)\fP |
\fIn(one)\fP.
Default: \fIboth\fP.
.TP
.B \-double(step)
Make real floppy drives double-step (35/40-track media in 80 track drive).
.B Linux only.
.TP
.B \-(emt)safe
Enable only safe emulation traps to block potentially dangerous functions
to the host system (Default).
.TP
\fB\-floppy\fP | \fB\-fdc\fP
Enable Floppy Disk Controller (Default).
.TP
\fB\-f(ore)g(round)\fP \fI0xRRGGBB\fP
Specifies foreground color of emulator window.
Default: white (\fI0xE0E0FF\fP).
.TP
.B -f(ull)s(creen)
Run in Fullscreen mode.
.TP
\fB\-guib(ack)g(round)\fP \fI0xRRGGBB\fP
Specifies background color of text based GUI window.
Default: dark green (\fI0x344843\fP).
.TP
\fB\-guif(ore)g(round)\fP \fI0xRRGGBB\fP
Specifies foreground color of text based GUI window.
Default: white (\fI0xE0E0FF\fP).
.TP
\fB\-halt\fP \fIaction\fP
Set action for Z80 HALT instruction:
\fId(ebug)\fP |
\fIh(alt)\fP |
\fIr(eset)\fP.
Default depends on the selected TRS-80 Model.
.TP
\fB\-h(ard)\fP\fIN filename\fP
Specifies name of hard disk image file to be inserted into
Hard\fIN\fP (0 - 3).
.TP
\fB\-h(ard)d(ir)\fP \fIdir\fP
Specify directory containing hard disk images.
Default: current directory.
.TP
.B \-hdboot
Patch Level II ROM for auto-boot from hard disk (Model I only).
.TP
\fB\-hideled\fP | \fB\-noled\fP
Hide disk activity and Turbo LED.
.TP
.B \-huff(man)
Enable Dave Huffman (and other) memory expansion for Model 4/4P.
.B Disables MegaMem, HyperMem and SuperMem.
.TP
.B \-hyper(mem)
Enable HyperMem (Anitek) memory expansion for Model 4/4P.
.B Disables Dave Huffman memory expansion and SuperMem.
.TP
\fB\-io(debug)\fP \fIhexval\fP
Set I/O port debug flags:
\fI01\fP = port input |
\fI02\fP = port output |
\fI04\fP = Hard Disk I/O |
\fI08\fP = Hard Disk Command.
.TP
\fB\-j(oy)s(tick)\fP \fInum\fP
Use USB joystick number \fInum\fP or \fIn(one)\fP as joystick.
.TP
.B \-k(ey)p(adjoy)
Use numeric keypad as joystick (Default).
.TP
\fB\-k(ey)s(tretch)\fP \fIcycles\fP
"Stretches" intervals between key transitions to \fIcycles\fP Z80 clock
cycles (T-states).
Default: \fI4000\fP.
.TP
.B \-le18
Emulate Lowe Electronics LE18 384x192 graphics adapter for Model I.
.TP
.B \-l(ower)c(ase)
Lower Case Modification Kit for TRS-80 Model I (Default).
.TP
\fB\-lubomir\fP | \fB\-lsb\fP
Enable Lubomir Soft Banker for Model I.
.B Disables Selector, SuperMem and X-MEM/80.
.TP
.B \-mega(mem)
Enable MegaMem (Anitek) memory expansion for Model III and 4/4P.
.B Disables Dave Huffman memory expansion.
.TP
\fB\-mem(size)\fP | \fB\-ram(size)\fP \fIKB\fP
Select memory size in KB (4 - 48) - Only for TRS-80 Model I/III.
Default: \fI48\fP.
.TP
.B \-micro(labs)
Model III or 4/4P: emulate Micro-Labs Grafyx Solution Hi-Res
graphics card.
.TP
.B \-m1
.TQ
.B \-m3
.TQ
.B \-m4
.TQ
.B \-m4p
Select TRS-80 model to emulate: I, III, 4 or 4P.
.TP
\fB\-m(odel)\fP \fIm\fP
Specifies TRS-80 model to emulate:
\fI1\fP or \fII\fP |
\fI3\fP or \fIIII\fP |
\fI4\fP or \fIIV\fP |
\fI4P\fP or \fIIVP\fP.
.RS
Default: Model I.
.RE
.TP
.B \-mouse(pointer)
Show mouse pointer for selection in emulator window (Default).
.TP
.B \-noa(spect)(ratio)
Disable aspect ratio of TRS-80 screen when resizing SDL2 window.
.TP
.B \-nodouble(step)
Turn off double-step mode for all real floppy drives (Default).
.B Linux only.
.TP
.B \-no(emt)safe
Allow potentially dangerous emulation traps.
Must be enabled to export files to the host. (\fBUSE WITH CAUTION\fP)
.TP
\fB\-nofloppy\fP | \fB\-nofdc\fP
Disable Floppy Disk Controller.
.TP
.B -nof(ull)s(creen)
Run in windowed mode (Default).
.TP
.B \-nohdboot
Do not patch Level II ROM for auto-boot from hard disk (Default).
.TP
.B \-nohuff(man)
Disable Dave Huffman (and other) memory expansion (Default).
.TP
.B \-nohyper(mem)
Disable HyperMem memory expansion (Default).
.TP
.B \-nok(ey)p(adjoy)
Do not use numeric keypad as joystick.
.TP
.B \-nole18
No emulation of LE18 graphic adapter (Default).
.TP
.B \-nol(ower)c(ase)
No lower case characters for TRS-80 Model I.
.TP
\fB\-nolubomir\fP | \fB\-nolsb\fP
Disable Lubomir Soft Banker for Model I (Default).
.TP
.B \-nomega(mem)
Disable MegaMem memory expansion for Model III and 4/4P (Default).
.TP
.B \-nomicro(labs)
Model III or Model 4/4P: emulate Radio Shack Hi-Res card (Default).
.RE
.TP
.B \-nomouse(pointer)
Hide mouse pointer and emulate joystick with mouse.
.TP
.B \-nor(e)s(ize)3
.TQ
.B \-nor(e)s(ize)4
Model III or 4/4P: always keep SDL2 window large enough for 80x24
text (640x240) putting a blank margin around outside.
.RS
Default: \fB\-resize3 \-noresize4\fP.
.RE
.TP
.B \-noscan(lines)
No scanlines in emulator screen (Default).
.TP
.B \-nosel(ector)
Disable Dutch TRS-80 Users Society Selector memory expansion (Default).
.TP
.B \-nos(hift)b(racket)
Emulate [, \, ], ^, and _ as unshifted keys, and {, |, }, and ~ as shifted.
Default for Model I and III.
.TP
\fB\-nosound\fP | \fB\-mute\fP
Disable Sound Output at startup.
.TP
\fB\-nostringy\fP | \fB\-noesf\fP
Do not emulate Exatron Stringy Floppy Drive for Model I (Default).
.TP
.B \-nosuper(mem)
Disable SuperMem memory expansion (Default).
.TP
.B \-no(true)dam
Opposite of \fB-truedam\fP (Default).
.TP
.B \-not(urbo)
Switch Turbo mode off (Default).
.TP
.B \-not(urbo)p(aste)
Disable Turbo mode temporarily while pasting from clipboard (Default).
.TP
.B \-noxmem(80)
Disable X-MEM/80 16K page memory expansion for Model I (Default).
.TP
.B \-pause
Pause the emulator at startup.
.TP
\fB\-p(rinter)\fP \fItype\fP
Select printer type:
\fI0\fP or \fIn(one)\fP |
\fI1\fP or \fIf(ile)\fP |
\fI2\fP or \fIt(ext)\fP.
Default: \fInone\fP.
.TP
\fB\-p(rinter)d(ir)\fP \fIdir\fP
Specify directory for printer output and screenshot files.
Default: current directory.
.TP
.B \-r(e)s(ize)3
.TQ
.B \-r(e)s(ize)4
Model III or 4/4P: resize window whenever emulated display mode
changes between 64x16 text (512x192) and 80x24 text (640x240).
.RS
Default: \fB\-resize3 \-noresize4\fP.
.RE
.TP
\fB\-r(om)(file)\fP \fIfilename\fP
Use romfile \fIfilename\fP for the selected TRS-80 Model with \fB-m(odel)\fP.
.TP
\fB\-r(om)(file)1\fP \fIfilename\fP
.TQ
\fB\-r(om)(file)3\fP \fIfilename\fP
.TQ
\fB\-r(om)(file)4p\fP \fIfilename\fP
Use romfile specified by \fIfilename\fP for the TRS-80 Model.
.TP
\fB\-s(ample)r(ate)\fP \fIrate\fP
Set sample rate for new cassette wav files, direct cassette I/O to sound
card, and sound output.
Default: \fI44100\fP.
.TP
\fB\-sc(ale)\fP \fIfactor\fP
Scale emulator window by \fIfactor\fP times:
\fI1\fP | \fI2\fP | \fI3\fP | \fI4\fP.
Default: \fI1\fP.
.TP
\fB\-s(cale)q(uality)\fP \fIquality\fP
Select render scale quality:
\fI0\fP (nearest) | \fI1\fP (linear) | \fI2\fP (best).
Default: \fI1\fP.
.TP
.B \-scan(lines)
Display scanlines to simulate an old CRT monitor resolution.
.TP
\fB\-(scan)shade\fP \fIbrightness\fP
Set brightness of scanlines (0 = dark - 255 = light).
Default: \fI127\fP.
.TP
.B \-sel(ector)
Enable Dutch TRS-80 Users Society Selector memory expansion for Model I.
.B Disables Lubomir, SuperMem and X-MEM/80.
.TP
\fB\-serial\fP \fIttyname\fP
Set tty device to be used for I/O to TRS-80's serial port.
Default: \fI/dev/ttyS0\fP.
.TP
.B \-s(hift)b(racket)
Emulate [, \, ], ^, and _ as shifted keys, and {, |, }, and ~ as unshifted.
Default for Model 4 and 4P.
.TP
.B \-(show)led
Show disk activity and Turbo LED at bottom of emulator screen (Default).
.TP
\fB\-size(map)\fP \fIz0[,z1,z2,z3,z4,z5,z6,z7]\fP
Selectively set whether drives are emulated as 5-inch or 8-inch.
.TP
.B \-sound
Enable Sound Output (Default).
.TP
\fB\-s(peedup)\fP \fIkit\fP
Select Speedup Kit or Banking:
\fIn(one)\fP |
\fIa(rchbold)\fP |
\fIb(anking)\fP |
\fIc(t-80)\fP |
\fIh(olmes)\fP |
\fIl(nw)\fP |
\fIs(eatronics)\fP |
\fIt(cs)\fP.
Default: \fIarchbold\fP.
.TP
\fB\-s(tate)d(ir)\fP \fIdir\fP
Specify directory containing emulator state and configuration files.
Default: current directory.
.TP
\fB\-step(map)\fP \fIs0[,s1,s2,s3,s4,s5,s6,s7]\fP
Selectively set double-step mode for individual real floppy drives.
.B Linux only.
.TP
\fB\-stringy\fP | \fB\-esf\fP
Emulate Exatron Stringy Floppy Drive for Model I.
.TP
\fB\-super(mem)\fP \fIsize\fP
Enable SuperMem (Alpha Technology) memory expansion for Model I/III/4/4P
with \fIsize\fP KB: \fI256\fP | \fI512\fP | \fI768\fP | \fI1024\fP or
\fI0\fP to disable (Default setting).
.B Disables Huffman, HyperMem, Lubomir, Selector and X-MEM/80.
.TP
\fB\-sw(itches)\fP \fIvalue\fP
Set sense switches on Model I serial port card.
Default: \fI0x6f\fP.
.TP
.B \-(true)dam
Turn off single density data address mark remapping kludges.
.TP
.B \-t(urbo)
Switch Turbo mode on.
.TP
.B \-t(urbo)p(aste)
Engage Turbo mode temporarily while pasting from clipboard.
.TP
\fB\-t(urbo)r(ate)\fP \fIfactor\fP
Set \fIfactor\fP of normal TRS-80 speed that the emulator runs in Turbo mode.
Default: \fI5\fP.
.TP
\fB\-w(afer)\fP\fIN filename\fP
Specifies name of stringy wafer image file to be inserted into
Wafer\fIN\fP (0 - 7).
.TP
.B \-xmem(80)
Enable X-MEM/80 16K page memory expansion (Michael Wessel) for Model I.
.B Disables Lubomir, Selector and SuperMem.
.TP
\fB\-y(ear)\fP \fIyear\fP
Set \fIyear\fP for TRS-80 time-of-day clock instead of the current year.
Default: \fI0\fP for current year.
